Former Senate President, Bukola Saraki has promised to create more than 40,000 jobs for youths if elected as the president of Nigeria in 2023. According to Saraki who is contesting on the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), job creation for youths is one of the real solutions he has to get Nigeria headed in the right direction. He said “Creating more than 40,000 job opportunities for youths is one of the real solutions I have implemented to get Nigeria headed in the right direction”. Earlier, Saraki had posted that he met with Sokoto state governor, Aminu Tambuwal, Governor Bala Mohammed of Bauchi and Samuel Ortom of Benue state in Makurdi for discussion on the unity of the party and Nigeria. He wrote “As part of our ongoing consultations with leaders and stakeholders in our party, PDP, towards building consensus, alongside my brothers Governor Aminu Waziri Tambuwal and Governor Bala Mohammed, I was in Makurdi to meet with Governor Samuel Ortom of Benue State”. “Our discussion on the need for unity within our party and the country went very well. We look forward to meeting with other leaders and stakeholders as we move forward”.